text_trans: On Tuesday (2nd), Lee Jae myung, the leader of South Korea's largest opposition party and common democratic party, was attacked while attending an event in Busan. He was cut and bled in the neck by a man disguised as a supporter with a knife. Lee Jae myung fell to the ground and was immediately taken to the hospital for treatment. He was still conscious at the time, and the perpetrator was subdued by the police and taken to a police car on the spot. text_trans: Japan's discharge is not nuclear wastewaterï¼Œ but rather nuclear wastewater. The concept of cooling water that has passed through the core of a nuclear reactor and cooling water that has not passed through the core are different. The former is called primary cooling waterï¼Œ while the latter is called secondary cooling water. Although it has not passed through the coreï¼Œ secondary cooling water also contains trace amounts of radioactivity. The main radioactive element is tritiumï¼Œ which can be directly discharged into the sea as long as it meets the safety standards of the International Atomic Energy Agency

text_trans: There are five measures to choose from for the treatment of Fukushima nuclear wastewater. Firstlyï¼Œ the evaporation of nuclear wastewater cannot be ignored for air pollution. Secondlyï¼Œ electrolysis and recycling consume huge amounts of electricity and require huge funds. Thirdlyï¼Œ deep well underground landfill will affect land quality. text_trans: Japan has started discharging filtered nuclear wastewater into the oceanï¼Œ which has been opposed and incited by the Chinese Communist Party.
